Mode Delegate port Use case Default (omit <code>delegateExecutor</code>) <code>MockA2ADelegateExecutor</code> CI, demos, offline development <code>A2ADelegateExecutor</code> HTTP submit + poll Production A2A agent runtimes <code>activity_execution_mode: host_mediated</code> None (host submits outcome) Assistant hosts that own agent credentials <p>Wire the production executor when constructing the application port or graph walker:</p> <pre><code>import { A2ADelegateExecutor, createWorkflowApplicationPort } from "@agent-workflow/engine";

const port = createWorkflowApplicationPort({
  store,
  delegateExecutor: new A2ADelegateExecutor({
    operatorConfig: {
      baseUrl: process.env.A2A_BASE_URL,
      apiKeyEnv: "A2A_API_KEY",
      pollIntervalMs: 500,
      pollTimeoutMs: 120_000,
    },
  }),
});
</code></pre>
